Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.52,0:04:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It knows where it is locally, but it doesn't really have any point of self-correction.\NSo if the instruments on the ship are off, the ship will be lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.40,0:04:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And over time, they have, of course, at the bottom of the Great Lakes are the wrecks of\N6,000 ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.18,0:05:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Just at the bottom of the Great Lakes, that's rather amazing.\NSo not having a compass to tell you truth from falsehood is why mankind barely survives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.63,0:05:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So the map of consciousness, then, is picking up on essence.\NOne of the main themes of these lectures is to differentiate appearance, what a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.46,0:05:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,looks like, or what you think about it, or what's your opinion in, from essence, which\Nis independent of what you think about it, or how it's pictured, or how it's projected
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.70,0:05:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,into the world.\NReality, then, is self-confirmatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.35,0:05:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So on a scale of 1 to 1,000, you can calibrate the relative energy of the essence of anything,\Nanywhere in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.26,0:06:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about consciousness, which is more comprehensible from quantum mechanics, is non-locality.\NThe essence of consciousness, it has no beginning, it has no end, it has no midpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.46,0:06:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no beginning.\NIt has no here, and it has no there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.49,0:06:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no now, and it has no then.\NI don't know what the heck all that means, but it sure sounds impressive, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.46,0:06:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In essence, it means we can calibrate the level of consciousness of Cleopatra, as well\Nas Mrs. Clinton, or what's that crazy lady on TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.02,0:06:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She rants and raves.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.90,0:06:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Rosie.\NRosie, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.70,0:06:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All her favorite people.\NI love Rosie, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.48,0:06:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can make millions being mad as a hatter, you know?\NIt's wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.48,0:06:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to be sane, logical, anything.\NThat's freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.88,0:06:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wonderful.\NThat's America.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.04,0:07:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God.\NSo we can calibrate, then, by consciousness picks up the essence of things, and the reason
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.36,0:07:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,it does so, because the evolution of life in this planet, as we've said before, the\Nmost primitive protozoa has no energy within itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.49,0:07:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like chlorophyll green plants just sit there and enjoy the sun.\NThat which is protoplasmic has to obtain energy from out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.83,0:07:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, it has to be able to diagnose what's edible and what's lethal, what will\Nkill you and what will support life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.28,0:07:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's an intuitive knowingness, you know, that it derives as an essence of life.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.58,0:07:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.58,0:08:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the secret of life itself, especially in its expression as protoplasm.\NOn this scale of consciousness, the way it turned out, the scale is arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.22,0:08:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We could have picked one to a million or any other number, but as long as it's the same\Npoint of reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.86,0:08:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's pretty much like a thermometer or an altimeter.\NAnd I have no personal feelings about calibrated numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.18,0:08:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Other times I hear critics, you know.\Nhe said this, or he said that, I didn't say anything, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.00,0:08:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't say anything about it.\NHe doesn't even care about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.40,0:08:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do I care what the pyramids in Egypt calibrate at?\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.80,0:08:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't own them or anything.\NSo I don't have any vested interest
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.29,0:08:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in what things calibrate at.\NHaving done tens of thousands of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.45,0:08:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we've gotten to be able to pretty much guess in advance\Nat least what range a thing is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.33,0:09:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But occasionally, we're surprised, too.\NThe presumption is that it would come out in a certain value,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.61,0:09:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and it comes out quite differently.\NIf so, then we look elsewhere to see
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.55,0:09:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the explanation of that.\NAnd of course, the one that upset some people
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.13,0:09:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,was we said that earth warming is not due to human at all.\NOh, the angry blogs and everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.01,0:09:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see people.\NF you, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.59,0:09:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think about it?\NI get such nice emails sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.52,0:09:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we got, no, earth warming is not due to pollution.\NWe had to look, why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.68,0:09:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And we looked deeper, and we found, yes,\Nit's due to magnetic solar activity,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.18,0:10:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the magnetic radiation of the surface of the sun.\NAnd our core drilling is down through 10,000 years
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.66,0:10:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't calibrate it.\NAnd now, that hit the news this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.38,0:10:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So as of this week, I'm an OK person in the world again.\NThank you, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.71,0:10:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to offend certain people, you know what I'm saying?\NSo one of the reasons people have difficulty discerning truth
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.16,0:10:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and reality is there's so much investment\Nin what they believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.11,0:10:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you want to stay free and become enlightened, don't pour\Na lot of emotion into any view.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.62,0:10:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you don't have to die for environmentalism\Nor, you know what I mean, some particular viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.67,0:10:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It supersedes reality.\NPeople throw all this intense emotion
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.51,0:10:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,into what they believe.\NIt's bad enough to even believe it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.07,0:11:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's even worse to throw a lot of emotion into it.\NIf Al Gore's book don't win, you're
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.13,0:11:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,going to die or kill yourself.\NYou should bomb the Pentagon or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NAnyway, be passionate for God, be passionate for God
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.40,0:11:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than political labeling and put on everything.\NBecause everything that's political in today's world,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.76,0:11:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't mention anything but it's got a label.\NAnd then all the passion that goes with that label,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.14,0:11:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying?\NOne reason not to get so passionately committed,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.52,0:11:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is because if it's proven wrong, you look like an idiot.\NThat's one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.82,0:11:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the good news is that NBC News and all those now\Nagree with the old doc here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.27,0:12:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He was right all along, wasn't he?\NMy god, I thought that would show him, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.12,0:12:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The octogenarians are going to start off with a bang.\NAll right, so we can calibrate the level
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.67,0:12:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of anything in the world.\NNow, only about a third, which I didn't know
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.91,0:12:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,when I first started all this, only about a third\Nof the people in the United States are capable of doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.61,0:12:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,To get the correct answer, you yourself\Nhave to be calibrated over 200, which
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.77,0:12:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,means you're more interested in truth than in falsehood.\NOnly a third of the people in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.24,0:12:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,are more interested in truth than in falsehood.\NHm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.49,0:12:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,More interested in being right than knowing what the truth is.\NSo that's called narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.00,0:12:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo what distorts the capacity to perceive essence rather
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.34,0:12:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,than appearance is a detached commitment to truth,\Nto reach God through truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.48,0:13:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And the pathway through God, you can\Nsort through everything ever written by man anywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.76,0:13:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in time and calibrate what's true and follow what's true.\NIt'll take you to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.92,0:13:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All truth will eventually take you to divinity.\NGod is the source and the essence of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.31,0:13:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which arises truth.\NSo if you do nothing, every time you come to a split in the road,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.55,0:13:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you follow which one calibrates to the higher.\NAnd you keep doing that, you'll end up God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.72,0:13:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth is a pathway to God.\NDevotion, all these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.24,0:13:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotion.\NBut devotion can lead you astray, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.36,0:13:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because people are devoted to Nazism,\Nnot devoted to all kinds of horrible things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.30,0:13:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotion to what?\NDevotion to truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.10,0:14:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So we call this the devotional nonduality.\NNonduality meaning you're beyond truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.72,0:14:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You find out what is the truth, and then you\Ndevote yourself to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.10,0:14:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So in your life, then, all you have to do is look up these things.\NAnd you can see those things that will bring you to God
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.13,0:14:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,are the highest, an inner joy, lovingness.\NReason precedes that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.11,0:14:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see that reason is beyond emotionality.\NReason doesn't have anything to do with emotionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.04,0:14:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer to a problem doesn't depend on how you feel about it,\Ndoes it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.47,0:14:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NSo reason is in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.79,0:14:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still emotionality in the 300s.\NAnd however, it's positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.80,0:14:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's positive, positive emotionality.\NAnd then below level 200, you have all the negatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.14,0:14:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,190 is pride.\NMost of the negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.13,0:15:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the blogs we get calibrate at 190.\NAnd those are like the guy who writes the books that disproves Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.25,0:15:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He's still writing them.\NHow he explains the atomic bomb, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.68,0:15:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So pridefulness, then, is at about 190.\NAnd then you get just hatefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.30,0:15:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we get some blogs that are just, I hate you.\NThat's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.58,0:15:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,At least he's honest.\NThen people hate things and think they love them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.74,0:15:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we'll move on.\NWe're just going to do a quick review.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.84,0:15:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the enlightened and divine states.\NAnd as you see, the higher you get,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.64,0:15:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment really starts at 600.\NThat's formally on that chart, 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.40,0:15:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's beyond the experience.\NReality is nonlinear as context rather than content.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.82,0:16:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you go all the way up.\NYou see, you go on up to 1,000 in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.09,0:16:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you go up to infinity.\NI don't know where the numbers are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.83,0:16:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We had numbers here.\NArchangels at 60,000 and up, 6,000 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.27,0:16:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, what the calibrated level of consciousness does\Nis confirm spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.55,0:16:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirm spiritual reality.\NConfirm it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.05,0:16:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't prove it.\NConfirms it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.91,0:16:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on, then.\NHere's the distribution of the consciousness in the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.95,0:16:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You see approximately 80% of the world calibrates below 200,\Nwhich explains the nature of the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.22,0:16:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, next.\NSo man is on an evolutionary pathway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.76,0:17:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So distribution of the levels of mankind, about 22% of mankind\Nis above 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.46,0:17:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And the great man.\NThe mass of mankind is below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.32,0:17:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, truth does not prevail in society.\NFalsehood prevails.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.31,0:17:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So why doesn't the world just destruct, then?\NWe'll go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.17,0:17:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't destruct because those above 200, you see,\Nis a logarithmic chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.19,0:17:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So the power of those above 200 is so enormous,\Nthat it balances the approximate 80% below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.54,0:17:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A group like this, which we've calibrated a number of times,\Nis enormously powerful in balancing out these energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.16,0:18:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So a group like this is right here.\NAnd because their power is exponentially, logarithmically
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.25,0:18:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,very high, it counterbalances negativity.\NNow, the negativity is very high.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.63,0:18:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very high.\NThey are greater in numbers, but their energy is far weaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.08,0:18:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So spiritual groups that are highly committed\Nhelp maintain the energy level of mankind overall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.50,0:18:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.\NAnd here is the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.03,0:18:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,over a timeline which you're going to have to throw out.\NBecause it recently took a dip down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.11,0:18:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently took a dip down.\NConsciousness of mankind is is brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.87,0:18:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of just dropped five or seven points in Western civilization, in the U.S., and\Nin the world in general.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.07,0:18:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's make a note.\NWe have to repair that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.21,0:18:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to go like this.\NI don't argue with God about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.12,0:19:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If he wants it to go like this, it'll go like that.\NIt'll go like that, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.56,0:19:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, this is just the evolution of the energy of life over great eons of time, great\Neons of time, and you can't see it from back there, so we'll go on to the next one, and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.92,0:19:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that evolution through the animal kingdom, you see?\NCan you imagine if this was a couple of million years ago, we'd be out there saying, save
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.80,0:19:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the dinosaurs, save Tyrannosaurus.\NAlex, save Tyrannosaurus, Alex, save Tyrannosaurus, Alex, save Tyrannosaurus, Rex.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.02,0:19:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so adorable, so cute.\NSo here we see the evolution of mankind then through life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.56,0:20:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Life can only originate from life itself.\NNo skeptic has ever been able to create life out of non-life, which is the downfall of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.97,0:20:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the materialistic.\NThe secularist is that life is a totally different energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.15,0:20:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It cannot arise from non-life, either organic or non-organic.\NSo life originates from a different source than the material world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.37,0:20:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we see all the animals and all our favorites that we've talked about over the\Nyears, Komodo dragon and the octopus.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.06,0:20:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Octopus is extremely intelligent.\NIt really should be more than 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.24,0:20:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't we pluck them up a little bit?\NThere was one on the octopus on TV the other night.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.30,0:20:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They're so smart.\NThey're just really brainy, you know, smarter than people, many often.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.23,0:20:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we go up through why dolphins calibrate different than whales.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.51,0:21:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Whales and dolphins.\NSometimes I'll get an argument in the email.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.27,0:21:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.83,0:21:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask me how come.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.53,0:21:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we come up through the evolution.\NThe evolution of the animals, animal kingdom, and you see the major shift at level 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.61,0:21:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,From the carnivore who lives by the death of others, eats others, to the herbivore, which\Nbecomes benign, so it's similar to our chart, 200 and up is benign, and less than 200 tends
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.19,0:21:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to be carnivorous, it'll kill you.\NAnd here we come up through all of our favorites.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.28,0:21:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Dogs.\NThere's something very special about dogs and family dogs and cats, because you see
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.12,0:22:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the cat's purr is at 500, and the dog's wagging tail is at 500.\NThere's something very, very special about them, spiritually speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.00,0:22:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Their capacity to love, loyalty, et cetera.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.04,0:22:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWe'll go on next.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.34,0:22:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo when we skip the negative and then we get up to low.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.14,0:22:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,level of truth, then we get up to the level of emotions, positive emotions, and then when\Nwe get to the consciousness level of the 400s, you leave the world of emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.41,0:22:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason and the intellect don't care how you feel about it at all.\NSome people try to mix the two, how they feel about facts and reality, and it's really irrelevant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.97,0:22:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,how you feel about it.\NSo these are the great books of the Western world, which are the foundation, the emergence
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.15,0:22:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Renaissance, the great intellect.\NIt's really a rebirth of what went on in ancient Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.85,0:23:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The high point of human civilization was really in ancient Greece, then it fell apart, and\Nthen it was resurrected.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.98,0:23:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's so.\NThe high point of human evolution, we have a person that asked this, was the intellectual
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.37,0:23:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,world.\NThe intellectual world was the foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.61,0:23:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellectual world was the ancient Greece.\NThat's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.67,0:23:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I was intuitive, but I never did the Aramon.\NSo then it was reborn in the Renaissance, and now these are all called dead white men,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.36,0:23:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess.\NThey don't allow them in the academia anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.58,0:23:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but this is the intellectual elegance all the way up to consciousness level 499.\N499 is the level of great geniuses, Sir Isaac Newton, Freud, Sir Isaac Newton, Freud,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.89,0:23:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,who else?\N499, Einstein, 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.31,0:24:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So 499 is as high as you can push the intellect.\NSo I have always had respect for this presentation of the development of the human intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.47,0:24:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,over time.\NBecause it's the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.37,0:24:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That differentiates man from the animal, yeah?\NI mean, animals can hate and animals can love.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.60,0:24:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So what makes you different is that you have a prefrontal cortex.\NSo we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.66,0:24:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of the prefrontal cortex is to think.\NLet's work.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.40,0:24:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we talk about content.\NSo here's to the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.18,0:24:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And content, what does it look like?\NIt depends on the proximate context, the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.50,0:24:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,A crime.\NAt the time, he was intoxicated and the lady's dog was biting his leg and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.74,0:25:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So proximate context influences our understanding of what went on.\NHe shot her, but he was drunk and she was attacking him with a knife, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.90,0:25:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the proximate context.\NThen the infinite context is consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.37,0:25:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth and understanding and reality.\NSo that's the proximate context.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.47,0:25:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And understanding and reality is to interpret content within context.\NSo one of the easiest ways to lie in our society, and it's done all the time, is to just ignore
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.61,0:25:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the context.\NIgnore the context, because that way you can make people wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.82,0:25:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you put it in the context, then you can't make them wrong.\NSo you know, say we were at war at the time, oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.16,0:25:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we'll move on to the next.\NThis I just put on for, not that I understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.31,0:25:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But it sure looks impressive, don't it?\NQuantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.18,0:26:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because quantum mechanics is in the linear domain or in the intellectual domain, coming\Ncloser and closer to an understanding of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.04,0:26:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And Henry Stapp, whose book you can get off, you can get for free, Henry Stapp, you can\Nprint out his book for free, his most recent book, you know, brings an approximation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.00,0:26:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, what he's emphasizing.\NAnd which I emphasize, is the effect of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.47,0:26:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The effect of intention.\NSo we say that this world does not operate according to the Newtonian laws of causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.55,0:26:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of this causing of that.\NInstead, there is a potential, a potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.19,0:26:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And under the proper conditions, meaning the proper context, the potentiality emerges as\Nan actuality, not as a result of causation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.05,0:26:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So the little seed is not caused.\NNobody forces it to grow into a blossom.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.37,0:27:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Under proper conditions, one of those being your intention for it to grow, the conditions\Nyou add are warmth, and sunlight, and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.93,0:27:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, like a pupa coming out of a cocoon, it emerges as a flower or a butterfly.\NBut nobody forces it to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.17,0:27:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody causes it.\NYou can take a cocoon and squeeze it and apply all the force you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.79,0:27:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't create a butterfly, you'll just create a mess.\NSo intention is very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.45,0:27:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you listen to the lecture with the intention\Nof advancing your own level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.59,0:27:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and doing it communally with all of us together,\Nthat is the likelihood that we'll develop, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.59,0:27:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So a group like this is very powerful\Nbecause of its intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.02,0:27:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so as I say, you can get this for yourself,\Nhappily, Henry Stapp, you can print it out for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.50,0:28:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go next.\NYes, the other difference that bothers people politically,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.56,0:28:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,everything bothers people politically,\Nis that the two levels, above and below 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.90,0:28:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,have a different brain physiology.\NThis is profoundly important.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.96,0:28:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 people process things.\NLeft brain dominance, completely differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.44,0:28:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They do it through the left side of the brain,\Nand these are the primarily animal responses.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.40,0:28:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal responses.\NSo things, this is how perception becomes distorted.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.55,0:28:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you perceive the world through the left brain,\Nbelow 200, you're seeing it more as an animal sees it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.93,0:28:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody agrees with you, they're a friend.\NIf they don't agree with you, you're an enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.89,0:29:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and have to attack them.\NPeople that don't like what we say here,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.97,0:29:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,read in the book, have a cup of whiskey and sodas,\Nthey sit down at the computer,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.02,0:29:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,F you, you dumb ass.\NIsn't that what they say sometimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.96,0:29:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She reads them.\NI'm not allowed to read them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.83,0:29:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The office staff won't let me.\NI say, what's that there?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.03,0:29:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to see this.\NAll right, so how does forgiveness come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.20,0:30:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgiveness is seeing error as limitation\Nbecause this is a physiologic limitation
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.46,0:30:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,due to brain function itself.\NThat's what Jesus Christ said,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.09,0:30:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to forgive because people who are not integrous\Ncannot help but be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.57,0:30:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Cannot help but be that way.\NSo the forgiveness then,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.41,0:30:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,people say forgiving is very hard to do.\NIt's not hard once you understand this,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.91,0:30:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that the person is limited\Nby their own brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.07,0:30:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And from this side, out this end comes F you.\NWe call a spade a spade in these lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.02,0:30:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And what did Jesus Christ say about them?\NHe said to avoid them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.72,0:31:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, don't attack evil.\NAvoid, do not become engaged with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.08,0:31:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not try to prove it that it's wrong.\NDon't go to war with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.22,0:31:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get into an argument.\NThrow their emails away.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.06,0:31:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't answer anything that calibrates under 200.\NThey bring in a message and say it was a calibrative set.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.20,0:31:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's under 200, we just throw it in the waste basket.\NWhat happens at consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.34,0:31:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which one arise at through karmic advantage\Nand devotion, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.02,0:31:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,through prayer and through forgiveness\Nand through the mercy of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.44,0:31:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is now the brain shifts sides\Nand there's the production of kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.69,0:32:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What shifts the brain chemistry from here to here\Nis the emergence of kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.33,0:32:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And with kundalini energy emerges the etheric body,\Nthe etheric brain, the etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.79,0:32:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So the processing that goes on here\Nis instantaneous through the etheric brain
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.25,0:32:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,before it even gets to the prefrontal cortex.\NAnd therefore, this person sees things differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.83,0:32:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the reasons they see things differently\Nis because that's their intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.67,0:32:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I see things differently now is a stock phrase in 12-step groups\Nof course of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.80,0:32:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody spiritually devoted will eventually\Nbegin to see things more benign and feel sorry for people
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.64,0:32:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than hate them, feel sorry for them.\NI don't hate the Komodo dragon, but I don't step
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.54,0:32:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,into his cage in my bare feet.\NSo it doesn't mean to be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.72,0:33:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I think it's misinterpreted\Nas being stupid and tell you, oh, Komodo dragons,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.20,0:33:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,they won't hurt you.\NThen they're OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.68,0:33:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They're OK.\NThat's the last thing they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.48,0:33:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So being blind to danger doesn't mean to be oblivious.\NYou can love the animal and not bother with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.72,0:33:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but I wouldn't get in the cage with them.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.81,0:33:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so below 200, then, you have a different,\Nthere's a columnist named Pitts, and he coined the term, which
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.68,0:33:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I've quoted in the current book,\Nthat these people on the left here
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.70,0:33:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,live in an alternate reality.\NThis is an alternate reality, and it's a different reality
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.72,0:33:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from this level here.\NOne reason it's different, it literally is.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.32,0:33:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Pitts was right, even though he's a columnist.\NThey actually have a different reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.82,0:34:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They process things differently.\NThey see them differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.78,0:34:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They experience them differently.\NOver here, you experience things more.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.11,0:34:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He's more benign, above 200.\NSo if something is destructive, out of respect,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.84,0:34:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,out of respect for his reality, I don't provoke it.\NSo that's respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.49,0:34:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I respect the Komodo dragon.\NSo I don't make them wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.09,0:34:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't hate them, but I respect them.\NSo unfortunately, sometimes idealism
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.68,0:34:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,reaches the point of being the fool.\NThinking that you can ignore the reality of what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.94,0:34:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see that's disrespectful?\NIf you don't think certain people in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.29,0:34:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,are out to kill you, you're not being respectful\Nof their belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.03,0:34:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I believe the international problems we have\Nis a failure to not only to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.85,0:35:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that different viewpoint, but to give it due respect,\Nto give it due respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.49,0:35:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody is carrying a loaded 45,\Nyou don't stick your fingers in his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.33,0:35:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He's always, that's disrespectful.\NOK.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.53,0:35:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So I believe in respecting one's energies.\NYour biggest safeguard is your respect for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.57,0:35:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because out of respect, then you feel\Nobligated to understand them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.05,0:35:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you understand them, you're not so likely\Nto stumble into offending.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.97,0:35:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, next one.\NGod versus science.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.58,0:35:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how this got in here.\NWe did God versus science.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.61,0:35:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't need to do that again.\NWe'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.22,0:35:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here we are at today.\NI knew we'd get to today somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.18,0:35:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What is real?\NWhat is real?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.34,0:36:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody thinks their mind knows what is truth.\NAnd we're going to do that next lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.74,0:36:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is real?\NSo I thought we'll start with just simple definitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.86,0:36:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What is real?\NFirst of all, there's a definition.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.78,0:36:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We say, well, it's actual.\NIt exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.10,0:36:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists.\NAnd mainly what we say is real is physical.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.60,0:36:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I really have 10 toes.\NYes, really have.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.44,0:36:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I had 10 toes in here.\NAnd so it's within the linear domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.00,0:36:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's linear, it can be confirmed by the senses.\NSo even the animal is capable of material linear reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.82,0:36:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fox can see.\NOr the hare.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.90,0:37:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's confirmable by the senses.\NSo you only need your left brain animal world to see whether a thing is in reality factual.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.47,0:37:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That is manifest.\NThen we jump to the next level from just sensory confirmation, the fox sees the rabbit there,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.56,0:37:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to mentalization.\NAnd we run into the world of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.73,0:37:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In science, for a thing to be real, it has to be, or true, it has to be measurable.\NSome, you know, it has to have dimensions, and it must exist somewhere in time and space.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.24,0:37:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, science is not really capable of dealing with the abstract.\NYou see that? All the answers to life will not come out of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.85,0:37:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The world that we deal with is adequately described by science,\Nwith its advance now to quantum mechanics and the Heisenberg principle,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.71,0:37:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it enlarges its realm.\NYou know, the current view of the universe is that the universe is held in place
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.97,0:38:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of consciousness itself.\NIt's consciousness itself that holds this world in its present state.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.26,0:38:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Without consciousness, the universe would not exist.\NSo all, as you read in Stapp's newest book,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.54,0:38:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole universe exists\Nwithin consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.54,0:38:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,within consciousness and because of consciousness.\NSo when you look at a thing, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.70,0:38:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you have delay going from potentiality to actuality.\NBy observation, you block the collapse of the wave function.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.21,0:38:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So the universe is suspended between potentiality and actuality\Nbecause we've collapsed the wave function at its present level, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.55,0:38:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all incorrect scientifically, so we'll forget it.\NWhat is real is confirmable by the senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.87,0:39:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Science then measures things via information about it,\Nsuch as measurement, time and place.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.87,0:39:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you look at, when you say,\NI think a thing is real,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.03,0:39:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you've really drawn a mental conclusion of your sensory experience.\NAnd it's really the lower mind in the animal that says it's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.03,0:39:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal doesn't have to think about it.\NYou're in, within you is an animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.88,0:39:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, within every human there's the animal.\NSo it's your animal that says the thing is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.88,0:39:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch, oh, oh, that's a stone.\NIt says it's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.88,0:39:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What it means is something else.\NTherefore, it's a subjective based on faith in sensory input.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.26,0:39:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What you say is real is based on your faith\Non your sensory input.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.87,0:40:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's therefore a subjective statement based on faith.\NTherefore, knocking faith means you would have no way
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.51,0:40:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of knowing anything about anything.\NYou have faith in your own sensory experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.51,0:40:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And throughout evolution then,\Nwe've developed the capacity to be able to sense
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.58,0:40:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the linear domain in a group.\NIt's a great level.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.61,0:40:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's also prone to errors we'll get to later.\NI am is provisional to consciousness levels above 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.79,0:40:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a mystification that people themselves are limited\Nin their level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.05,0:40:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 they exist and they are sensory,\Nbut they are unaware of their existence as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.50,0:40:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't say I exist, it just is.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.92,0:41:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see,\Nif you don't realize the value of life as a gift,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.18,0:41:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as existence itself,\Nthen you don't value it in others.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.18,0:41:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see cultures that destroy life of others\Nbecause they themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.43,0:41:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,although they exist as an animal,\Nthey're not really aware of their existence as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.46,0:41:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the sensory world is based on interpretation of data.\NThe argument about what's real
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.90,0:41:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's not,\Nwe'll run it through again when we get to what's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.90,0:41:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And we did run through it once before\Nwhen we talked about relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.90,0:41:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the intellectual problem is,\NPythagoras, as reported in Plato,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.41,0:41:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,says,\Nthe world I experience is real to me
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.50,0:42:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and the world that you experience is real to you.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.62,0:42:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no absolute reality.\NAll reality is only subjective,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.22,0:42:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which is really the basis of solipsism,\Nthat the way I experience the world is my world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.42,0:42:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it ends up with,\Nactually, the intellectual argument,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.86,0:42:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,philosophic argument,\Nends up with an absurdity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.66,0:42:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because the fact that you say you exist and I exist\Ndoesn't mean that neither one of us does.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.10,0:42:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There are two, actually.\NSocrates, of course, then brought this further
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.06,0:42:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and pointed out how illusion is perceived as a reality.\NAnd Socrates is a great friend to spiritual students
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.06,0:43:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because he gives you an avenue\Nby which forgiveness comes about through understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.47,0:43:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you forgive people\Nbecause, as Socrates said,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.47,0:43:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,illusion, then, is your perception of reality\Nand it's projected out into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.86,0:43:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What you want, you see.\NWhat you desire, you see as the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.98,0:43:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the trouble is you cannot see truth from falsehood.\NAnd this was further elaborated, of course, by Descartes,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.05,0:43:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,who pointed out, you know,\Nthere's the world within
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.05,0:43:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there's the world without\Nand the comprehension of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.05,0:43:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,depends, then, on transcending that duality.\NNow, the only way to transcend these dualities
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.05,0:43:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,pointed out throughout time\Nfrom Jesus Christ on through Socrates, Descartes, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.05,0:43:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or Protagoras,\Nthe only way to transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.01,0:44:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the possibility of making an error\Nabout reality or truth
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.39,0:44:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is, frankly, consciousness calibration.\NThere's absolutely...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.65,0:44:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,man has never, until now, evolved a way\Nto transcend that duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.65,0:44:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Never.\NNever.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.97,0:44:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All of mankind's history,\Nhe's never been able to discern
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.97,0:44:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,essence from appearance.\NAnd now, we have a very simple scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.50,0:44:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like he never could tell altitude\Nuntil somebody discovered an altimeter
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.50,0:44:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and now it's simple.\NSo, we don't have any opinion or view on things.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.50,0:44:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We just calibrate what is the level of truth,\Nwhat is the essence of that which is being described.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.50,0:44:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can be completely determined\Nand detached from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.17,0:44:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, what we think is real\Nis a sensory and a mental presumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.90,0:44:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we have a review of what I just said.\NThe universe is purely a mentalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.90,0:45:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no out there, only in here.\NIt's only in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.90,0:45:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no you and then the universe.\NSo, how do you prove what's real?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.82,0:45:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's through consensual validation.\NIf I say a thing weighs so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.82,0:45:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you weigh it and you get the same,\Nthen we both agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.82,0:45:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't create a reality,\Nbut that creates an agreement
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.82,0:45:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,on what both of us presumed to be a reality.\NStill does not tell you what's real,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.82,0:45:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but it tells you what is confirmable\Nwithin the usual definition of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.46,0:45:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next slide?\NOkay, so what we did now
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.38,0:45:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is review up to the present time\Nwe just got through saying
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.70,0:45:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,reality is subjective\Nbased on faith in one's senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.70,0:46:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's experiential of one's senses.\NTherefore, an animal is capable
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.70,0:46:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of discerning what's real.\NHe doesn't discern what's truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.70,0:46:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but he gets what's real.\NAnd it's dependent on the reliability
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.82,0:46:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of the information that your senses are giving you.\NSo, therefore, it's actually a testimonial.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.30,0:46:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All statements about reality\Nare a testimonial.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.10,0:46:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to get somebody else\Nto get rid of their argument,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.30,0:46:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,just say, call it,\Nit's just a testimonial.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.62,0:46:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a testimonial.\NWe all say that it fulfills
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.40,0:46:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the criteria of facts,\Nwhich is reliable data.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.40,0:46:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To know what is real\Nis a subjective presumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.72,0:46:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's mind says,\Nwell, I know what's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.72,0:46:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what's real.\NAnd we've become more
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.72,0:46:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or a little humble, more humble,\Nwhen we realize that that's the presumption
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.72,0:47:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that this mind is making now.\NAnd we always leave room
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.82,0:47:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for correction later.\NSo a sophisticated spiritual student
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.58,0:47:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,drops a lot of their narcissism\Nand instead takes on a certain humility
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.61,0:47:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that whatever I think and believe now\Ncould change later
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.61,0:47:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because additional information comes in.\NSo as spiritually committed people,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.90,0:47:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we tend to be somewhat more humble\Nabout our statements about the world
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.96,0:47:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and know that it's subject\Nto editing later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.96,0:47:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How many planets are there?\NWell, there were nine,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.82,0:47:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and now there's eight, right?\NSo we're somewhat humble then.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.69,0:47:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So intellectual humility\Nthen serves
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.75,0:47:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual purpose\Nthat we're not so dead sure
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.75,0:48:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're absolutely right\Nabout everything all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.75,0:48:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a likelihood, a presumption.\NSo all information then
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.75,0:48:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in a spiritual context\Nis held as presumptive,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.75,0:48:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's only provable\Nby actually becoming,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.88,0:48:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,by actually becoming.\NFulfills properties of content, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.66,0:48:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to tell me\Nwhen it's time for a break?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.66,0:48:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.78,0:48:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll finish up this slide.\NTo know what is real
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.64,0:48:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is a subject of resumption.\NAnd therefore, with humility,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.64,0:48:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so we talk about humility\Nin spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.64,0:48:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality means an openness\Nto receive.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.64,0:48:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I've often said,\Nit's yin in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.64,0:48:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's yin in nature.\NAnd certainty is like yang.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.70,0:48:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know that,\Nand I know that,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.70,0:48:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know that,\Nand no worth warming
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.70,0:49:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is up to evil Americans at all.\NI mean, that's very yang.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.70,0:49:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't leave any room\Nto back off gracefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.09,0:49:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Tentative means,\Nit seems to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.09,0:49:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,even now,\Nit seems to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.09,0:49:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that the temperature variation\Nof the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.22,0:49:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is likely due\Nto the magnetic activity
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.22,0:49:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of the surface of the sun.\NBut even now,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.50,0:49:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't say it's certain,\Neven though it's been
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.50,0:49:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,scientifically proven.\NI say it's likely,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.50,0:49:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because that could change\Ntomorrow, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.50,0:49:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't want to catch\Nin all our chips,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.86,0:49:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so...\NIn the Vegas of spiritual work,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.86,0:49:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't put all your chips\Non one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.86,0:49:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NTo know what is real
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.92,0:49:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is, therefore,\Na subjective presumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.92,0:49:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's best not to invest\Nnarcissistic emotionality into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.92,0:49:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Look how difficult it is\Nto get off a position
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.92,0:50:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,when you've poured\Nall kinds of emotional energy into it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.92,0:50:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and become sort of\Na fanatic about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.92,0:50:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why people\Njust can't have a view
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.92,0:50:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,about a thing\Nwithout becoming maniacal about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.92,0:50:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NYou want to change
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.92,0:50:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a little thing,\Nthey have a whole parade,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.92,0:50:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nand what are they going to have,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.92,0:50:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a summit aid or something?\NPeople are out there
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.92,0:50:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with parades\Nand all kinds of...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.92,0:50:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What's all the emotion about?\NWhy contaminate,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.11,0:50:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nthe intellectual world
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.11,0:50:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,with emotion?\NAnyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.71,0:50:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to know what is real\Nis a subjective presumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.71,0:50:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And with humility,\Nwe say it's a likelihood.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.97,0:50:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And all we're talking about anyway\Nis content.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.97,0:50:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And what it really means,\Nwe haven't even gotten to it yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.97,0:50:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because what it means\Nis signified as
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.97,0:50:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a consequence of context.\NSo it's a product
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.10,0:50:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of the sensory world,\Nthat's the animal world.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.10,0:50:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you add human mental processing\Nand editing.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.10,0:51:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nall information is itself
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.35,0:51:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,only tentative and provisional.\NEverything I say today
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.35,0:51:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is tentative and provisional.\NIt is the best understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.35,0:51:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have at the moment,\Nyou see?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.35,0:51:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,To think you know\Nis a narcissistic premise.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.35,0:51:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually,\Nyou know about,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.35,0:51:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you can know about a thing.\NThe only way to know a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.35,0:51:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be it.\NThe only one who knows
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.57,0:51:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is to be a cat\Nis a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.08,0:51:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only one\Nwho knows what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.08,0:51:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a cat\Nis a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.08,0:51:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only one\Nwho knows
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.08,0:51:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is\Nto be a cat
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.37,0:51:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is a cat.\NAnd the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.37,0:51:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,who knows\Nwhat it is to be a cat
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.37,0:51:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is a cat.\NYou can know about a cat,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.37,0:51:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but you cannot know.\NTo actually know
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.62,0:51:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.52,0:51:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And this brings us\Nto a very sophisticated
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.52,0:51:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,philosophic\Nand metaphysical understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.52,0:51:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That reality\Nis identity
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.52,0:51:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than description.\NThis is where
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.13,0:52:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we run into\Na political problem
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.13,0:52:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States.\NReality is
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.26,0:52:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what a thing is\Nrather than
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.26,0:52:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,how it is described.\NIn our world
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.64,0:52:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of the media,\Nwe no longer see
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.80,0:52:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what a thing is.\NWe see how
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.80,0:52:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it's politicized,\Nglamorized,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.80,0:52:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,presented,\Nwhether it's
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.82,0:52:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in technicolor,\Nwhether it has music,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.82,0:52:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's\Nscantily dressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.45,0:52:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Vote for.\NOh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.90,0:52:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If the world\Nwas all women,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.34,0:52:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd be on there\Nsaying,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.59,0:52:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,vote for.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.30,0:53:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,reality\Nis definition
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.32,0:53:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,by identity\Nrather than
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.45,0:53:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a description.\NWe can know
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.70,0:53:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,about the cat,\Nbut only the cat
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.70,0:53:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,knows\Nwhat it is
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.70,0:53:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a cat.\NAnd we've used
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.70,0:53:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,this example before.\NYou can read
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.93,0:53:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a cat,\Neverything you read
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.93,0:53:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,about cats\Nin the encyclopedia
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.22,0:53:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and say,\Nthe cat,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.22,0:53:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you think\Nof all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.22,0:53:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And the cat says,\Nwell,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.22,0:53:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not,\NI mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.22,0:53:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that's interesting,\Nbut it's not
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.22,0:53:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,got anything\Nto do with me
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.22,0:53:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NNow,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.92,0:53:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,what does the cat\Nexperience?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.92,0:53:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The cat experiences\Nonly that
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.92,0:53:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I am me.\NThe only reality
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.92,0:53:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nis that you are
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.92,0:53:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I am me.\NEverything else
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.27,0:53:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is a description.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.50,0:53:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,reality then\Nis identity
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.50,0:53:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than\Ndescription.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.50,0:53:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is important\Nto the mystic
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.62,0:53:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because\None becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.72,0:54:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,what\Na religionist
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.42,0:54:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,would describe.\NIt's no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.42,0:54:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,describable.\NIn fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.83,0:54:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't\Neven,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.83,0:54:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't\Ndescribe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.25,0:54:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Any attempt\Nto mystical
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.91,0:54:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,transmitting\Ninformation
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.91,0:54:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,about the\Nmystical
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.58,0:54:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,self-awareness\Nis frankly
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.58,0:54:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,impossible.\NFor one thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.58,0:54:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nobody\Nthere to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.78,0:54:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,describe it,\Nwhich is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.78,0:54:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,not even\Ncomprehensible
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.78,0:54:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to the average\Nperson either.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.78,0:54:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody thinks\Nthere's a you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.78,0:54:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody thinks\Nthere's a you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.96,0:54:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there.\NBecause they think
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.96,0:54:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a you,\Nthey project that
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.96,0:54:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and assume\Nthat there's a you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.25,0:54:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,there.\NThere's no you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.81,0:54:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,here at all.\NIf that's true
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.45,0:54:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of me,\Nthat's true
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.45,0:54:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of you\Nalso.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.95,0:55:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The highest levels\Nof consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.80,0:55:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no you-tube.\NThey really mean
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.53,0:55:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,me-tube.\NThere is no
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.53,0:55:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,actual me,\Nyou see,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.53,0:55:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because what you\Nconcern as you
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.53,0:55:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as me\Nends up
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.53,0:55:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as a definition.\NAnd when you
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.53,0:55:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,let go of definitions,\Nthat's the reality
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.53,0:55:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of your existence.\NThe reality
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.56,0:55:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of your existence\Nabout which nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.56,0:55:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,can be said.\NYou can't even
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.56,0:55:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,prove that you\Nexist without
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.78,0:55:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,going through\Na mentalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.23,0:55:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you\Nprove it will
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.58,0:55:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,kill you\Nanyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.58,0:55:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so.\NMahatma
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.58,0:55:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Maharshi\Nsaid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.68,0:55:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The world\Nyou see
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.68,0:55:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't even\Nexist.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.87,0:55:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's surely\Na projection.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.87,0:55:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course\Nthat's true
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.03,0:55:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at consciousness\Nlevel 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.03,0:55:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The world\Nyou see
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.03,0:55:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't even\Nexist.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.90,0:56:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is\Na dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.90,0:56:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't\Nmake sense
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.46,0:56:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to level\N700.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.78,0:56:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore\Ntry to
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.78,0:56:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,twist your mind\Ninto seeing
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.78,0:56:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it how Ramana\NMaharshi
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.78,0:56:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,sees it\Ndoesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.94,0:56:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually\Nwhat you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.94,0:56:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,do is you\Nlet go
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.94,0:56:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,giving reality\Nto the linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.94,0:56:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And by\Ndetachment
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.94,0:56:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,from linearity\Nthen
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.94,0:56:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you become\Ndetached
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.94,0:56:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and that\Nworld no
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.94,0:56:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,longer exists\Nas a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.07,0:56:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What's\Nthe next
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.70,0:56:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,slide,\Neh?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.26,0:56:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.\NWe say
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.26,0:56:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,for a thing\Nto be real
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.26,0:56:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to\Nexist in
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.39,0:56:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,a linear\Ndimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.39,0:56:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's\Nsort of
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.39,0:56:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,prosaic\Nscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.39,0:56:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,However\Nmany things
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.39,0:56:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,are real\Nthat do
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.39,0:56:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,not exist\Nwithin the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.39,0:56:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,physical\Ndimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.39,0:57:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Mental\Nreality
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.39,0:57:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you have\Na picture
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.42,0:57:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you have\Na reason
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.42,0:57:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in your\Nhead
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.90,0:57:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you have\Nimages
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.90,0:57:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,imagination\Nso these
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.90,0:57:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,are real\Nbut you
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.90,0:57:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,can't\Nprove
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.90,0:57:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,them.\NSo trying
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.90,0:57:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to reduce\Nreality
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.90,0:57:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to the\Npseudo
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.90,0:57:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,scientific\Nprimitive
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.90,0:57:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,then\Nit
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.90,0:57:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't\Nwork
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.06,0:57:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because\Nnot
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.06,0:57:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it's\Nnot
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.15,0:57:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a\Nreality
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.15,0:57:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in which\Nyou cannot
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.15,0:57:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,be confirmed\Nscientifically.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.15,0:57:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see\Nthe limitation
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.15,0:57:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of science\Nbecause a
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.15,0:57:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of\Npeople
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.15,0:57:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,will try\Nto refute
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.15,0:57:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual\Nreality
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.15,0:57:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and they\Ncome from
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.15,0:57:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of\Na pedestrian
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.15,0:57:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,level of\Nscience,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.18,0:57:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the level\Nof the
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.18,0:57:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,skeptic\Nsort of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.28,0:58:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which is\Nvery
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.28,0:58:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,important\Nto the
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.28,0:58:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,experience\Nso
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.28,0:58:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we could\Nsay that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.28,0:58:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,reality\Nis what
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.28,0:58:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you\Nexperience
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.28,0:58:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is real.\NSo we
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.28,0:58:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,come back\Nto
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.28,0:58:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Protagoras\Nmake full
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.28,0:58:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,circle\Nback
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.28,0:58:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to his\Ndiscussion
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.28,0:58:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,with\NPlato.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.28,0:58:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's\Nreal
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.28,0:58:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to you\Nis real
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.73,0:58:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to you\Nand what's
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.98,0:58:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,real\Nto me
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.98,0:58:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is the\Nemotional
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.98,0:58:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and what\Nyou actually
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.98,0:58:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,end up\Nwith is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.98,0:58:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if you've\Nremoved all
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.17,0:58:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the sources\Nof error
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.17,0:58:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what you end\Nup with
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.17,0:58:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is a scale\Nof consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.17,0:58:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've\Ndone it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.17,0:58:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I've taken\Neverything ever
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.17,0:58:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,written about\Nthe subject
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.17,0:58:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and transcended\Nit,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.36,0:58:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,canceled\Nit out,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.36,0:58:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,gone\Nbeyond
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.36,0:59:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it and\Nthe only
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.36,0:59:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,thing you\Nend up
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.49,0:59:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,with is\Na scale
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.49,0:59:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness\Nand it's
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.55,0:59:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because of\Nthat consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.03,0:59:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that holds\Nit
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.50,0:59:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,between\Nthe potential
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.50,0:59:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the\Nactual
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.52,0:59:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is partly\Nthe result
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.52,0:59:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of the\NZeno effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.52,0:59:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nwhen you
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.52,0:59:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend\Nthe emotional
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.52,0:59:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,all this\Nmentalization
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.68,0:59:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,all the things\Nwe've
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.68,0:59:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,talked\Nabout so
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.84,0:59:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,far\Nall you
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.84,0:59:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,end up\Nwith is
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.22,0:59:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a scale\Nof consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.22,0:59:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's\Nvery important
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.22,0:59:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand\Nthe difference
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.22,0:59:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,between reality\Nand illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.22,0:59:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,between perception\Nand essence
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.22,0:59:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and some\Nof the questions
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.22,0:59:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that have\Ncome at
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.29,0:59:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the end of\Nprevious lectures
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.33,0:59:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I realize\NI have
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.33,1:00:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,failed.\NYou've
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.33,1:00:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,failed\Nto have
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.42,1:00:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,gotten across\Nthe difference
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.42,1:00:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,between\Nperception
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.42,1:00:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and essence.\NPerception
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.42,1:00:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and essence.\NEssence
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.42,1:00:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and how\Nit's
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.42,1:00:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,differentiated\Nfrom appearance.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.42,1:00:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Noh my god
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.65,1:00:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,my brain's\Nall fagged
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.65,1:00:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,out.\NWell we went
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.78,1:00:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,through the\Nintellectual
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.78,1:00:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we went\Nthrough the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.78,1:00:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning\Nof the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.78,1:00:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,representation\Nbecause every
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.78,1:00:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,time I like\Nto recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.78,1:00:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it so it\Nbecomes innate
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.78,1:00:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,after you\Nhear it
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.78,1:00:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,enough\Nyou don't
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.78,1:00:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,have to\Nreason
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.78,1:00:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because if\Nyou go up
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.78,1:00:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in a plane\Nand try and
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.78,1:00:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,memorize\Nthe map
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.78,1:00:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of what you've\Nseen
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.78,1:00:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and go back\Ndown and try
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.78,1:00:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to memorize\Nit you'll
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.70,1:00:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,have to go\Nover that
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.70,1:00:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,field over\Nand over
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.70,1:00:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,again but\Nif you go up
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.70,1:01:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in a plane\Nand you've
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.70,1:01:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,gone over\Nthat terrain
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.70,1:01:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,many times\Nyou know
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.70,1:01:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly\Nwhere to
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.70,1:01:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,turn.\NYou know
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.70,1:01:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you turn\Naround and
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.70,1:01:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nwhere to
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.70,1:01:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,go.\NIt's just
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.70,1:01:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,obvious due\Nto familiarity
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.70,1:01:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,right?\NAnd save
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.70,1:01:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody\Nthinking I
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.70,1:01:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want\Npeople to
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.70,1:01:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,get stuck\Nin thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.70,1:01:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,or understanding.\NYou get
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.70,1:01:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,there by\Nfamiliarity
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.70,1:01:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because with\Nfamiliarity
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.70,1:01:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you bypass\Njust the
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.70,1:01:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,intellect\Nand all
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.70,1:01:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of your\Nfaculties
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.70,1:01:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which are\Nenormous
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.02,1:01:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to consciousness\Nit's obvious
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.02,1:01:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't it?\NI mean you don't
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.02,1:01:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,have to even\Nthink about
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.02,1:01:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it you know.\NI don't want
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.02,1:01:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,people thinking\Nabout anything
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.02,1:02:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we said.\NAlright so
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.26,1:02:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll take\Na break.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.41,1:02:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody wrote\Nme that
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.66,1:02:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Pepsi Cola\Nwould kill
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.66,1:02:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,me.\NIf you think
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.62,1:02:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that don't\Ndrink it
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.62,1:02:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,because it\Nwill.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.16,1:02:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are\Nwe?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.74,1:02:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Back to\Nwhere we
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.74,1:02:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,started\Na few
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.74,1:02:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,minutes\Nago.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.74,1:02:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't\Nthink
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.02,1:02:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody\Nwas
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.02,1:02:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,going\Nto
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.38,1:02:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,drink\NPepsi
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.38,1:02:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Cola.\NI think
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.38,1:02:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody\Nis going
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.73,1:02:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to drink\NPepsi
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.73,1:02:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Cola.\NWe're
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.73,1:02:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,going\Nto drink
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.73,1:02:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Pepsi\Nand keep
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.86,1:03:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,our\Nspirits
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.86,1:03:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,fresh.\NWe're
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.86,1:03:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,going\Nto
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.86,1:03:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,drink\NSome of them are famous names, professors and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.65,1:03:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you calibrate why is it they can't do it,\Nyou get because they're actually atheists.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.91,1:03:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you negate truth,\Nthen you don't have the privilege of access to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.29,1:03:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you negate truth,\Nthen you lose the capacity to discern truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.00,1:03:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAs you can see, we're negating all these various pathways
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.83,1:03:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to knowingness through the intellect,\Nthrough what you think is real, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.20,1:03:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And next time we'll get to what people think is truth.\NAnd you end up with a condition known as divine stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.18,1:04:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, divine stupidity is much to be desired.\NI remember ending up in divine stupidity myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.87,1:04:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, in the spiritual traditional literature,\Nit's described as a state.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.84,1:04:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Divine stupidity.\NI, myself, know nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.39,1:04:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because whatever you think is a definition,\Nall definitions are not factual.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.93,1:04:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what you are.\NWhat you are is sufficient statement
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.20,1:04:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,about which you say nothing.\NYou no longer say I am this or I am that or this is that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.23,1:04:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You experience like the cat does.\NThat which you are, you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.82,1:04:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's nothing.\NThere's nothing you can say about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.48,1:05:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you end up with divine stupidity.\NI'm sure if you asked Ramana Maharshi what he thought
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.47,1:05:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,about something, he'd tell you he had no idea.\NBecause you give up those little thought bundles.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.40,1:05:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And because you see them, that they're just thoughts,\Nthat they're evanescent, and that they have no intrinsic reality
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.28,1:05:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,other than the belief.\NIn fact, the only reason you believe this sensory information is
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.38,1:05:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because you have faith in God.\NYou have faith in belief that they're telling you what's true,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.22,1:05:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're telling you what's true.\NSo you end up then with divine stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.19,1:05:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, the more lectures you attend, the dumber you will get.\NSomebody says, what do you think about so-and-so?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.67,1:05:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And you tell them, I don't know.\NI just don't think about it at all, to tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.77,1:06:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think, I just don't have, I don't know.\NI just don't think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.63,1:06:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to think about it.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.78,1:06:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All you can say is what you've heard.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.35,1:06:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you see, that's a different dimension.\NI have heard such and such.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.14,1:06:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And even the Buddha related that.\NI have heard thus and so.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.20,1:06:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Even spiritual knowledge, all you can say, I have heard.\NSo I have heard, you see, is a much more humble position.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.04,1:06:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I have heard that such and such is so.\NAnd now, through my own inner work, I will arrive
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.08,1:06:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,at whether or not I have heard such and such.\NWhether that is true or not, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.75,1:06:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, in the world, there are those who can hear\Nand those who cannot hear.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.02,1:06:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, lectures such as the one here are heard by some\Nand not heard by others.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.94,1:07:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, the other dictum that went with it is that those\Nwho can hear, hear.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.41,1:07:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't worry about those who cannot hear,\Nthat's god's problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.50,1:07:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that, you don't have to...\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.00,1:07:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to they'll save you the whole trip of saving the world saving the\Nwhales saving the dinosaurs saving mankind say salvation is up to God yes
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.53,1:07:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can improve the pleasantry of living here but so divine stupidity you\Nend up with no opinion on anything because you see all opinions are just
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.70,1:07:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,mentalizations and you can change your opinion depending on the folks you're\Nhanging out with what happens to be beneficial what happens to be the meme
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.67,1:08:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of the day the meme of the day and they come and go so we even give reality then\Nto that which is evanescent such as a dream or a memory what is real we
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.34,1:08:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,give emotions reality yeah what reality does an emotion have an animal has\Nemotion so people who are big enthusiasts about emotion I would say
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.60,1:08:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what of what value is that to have a lovingness towards all of life\Nand all of its expression covers everything and everything is merely
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.56,1:08:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,upsetting because it's an interference you'll notice most anger is really an\Nupset
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.34,1:08:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll notice most anger is really an upset\Nthat you always put the mayonnaise here and somebody moved to there
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.08,1:09:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean that's the that's the big upset who moves my mayonnaise your home it's\Nwho moved the pickled herring where's my pickle Larry the quiet the angry
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.12,1:09:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,beast\Nshe says here's the fickle hearing okay so you see these passing things are of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.78,1:09:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,no great moment and there's no point in killing yourself or them\NI think I'll kill myself if I can't find the big old herring.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.85,1:09:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So the emotional, then, is depending on how seriously we see these things.\NIf we see them as trivial and evanescent, then we know that they're going to work out.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.71,1:09:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason they work out is because of unconditional love.\NSo even though the other person did it wrong and shouldn't have put the mayonnaise in the wrong place,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.20,1:10:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we're willing to forgive them because when I can't find my pickled herring,\Nshe knows where it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.33,1:10:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the context, so that's why we talk about relationship is alignment.\NThe two people alignment rather than involved.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.77,1:10:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of a push-pull ego battle, you see, of who's going to be in control,\Nwhen people are both aligned, neither one wants the other one to be upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.22,1:10:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the two are aligned with peace, and therefore the decision that is made\Nis one that tries to resolve issues rather than prolong them or inflame them further.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.59,1:10:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So content, then, is our understanding of content depends on the context,\Nwhether a certain thing is right or wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.21,1:11:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So today's world, what you see is a struggle for moral superiority.\NMoral superiority.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.97,1:11:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all this world is about.\NWho's right and who has the moral high ground.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.13,1:11:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you don't think I have the moral high ground, I'll kill you.\NThe moral high ground.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.86,1:11:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, it's constant.\NThe evening news is comical,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.90,1:11:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which everything is twisted a little bit to give it a moral high ground twist, you know, moral high ground.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.79,1:11:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So then, it's subject to the context.\NNow, spiritual, we, these are what are real to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.60,1:11:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is faith, hope, devotion, prayer, commitment, devotion, those are real.\NThose, of course, are all intangible, not provable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.86,1:12:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So to disparage them is because people are coming from the wrong realm.\NThese can either be proven or disproven.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.76,1:12:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I say, the skeptic ridicules faith.\NAnd has tremendous faith in his skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.11,1:12:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He lives and dies by his skepticism.\NI mean, has he got faith, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.43,1:12:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to kick this big rigmarole he writes about faith, you know.\NNobody's a bigger sucker for faith than the skeptic, you know, the cynic.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.90,1:12:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo these states to divine idiocy, divine stupidity, go through humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.16,1:12:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization of one's limitation.\NThe awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.98,1:12:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The awareness of it.\NAnd by observation and mindfulness, you see the mind taking off in these various directions.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.61,1:13:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So mindfulness is then a spiritual practice to be aware of where you are at all times.\NTo be aware of what your mind is doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.54,1:13:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, eventually, as you let go of everything and through contemplation,\Nyou begin to realize what the mind is, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.40,1:13:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mind is like addicted to experiencing.\NOh, it's hooked.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.31,1:13:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to experience.\NIt tries to extract experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.86,1:13:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the way it's going to survive.\NSo enlightenment is when your awareness, when your observation gets beyond experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.30,1:13:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The leading edge of this.\NThe experiencer takes place in one ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.18,1:14:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Within one ten-thousandth of a second, the mind has already interpreted the incoming stimulus.\NIt jumps in there and categorizes it, makes it right, makes it wrong, makes it attractive, has an aversion.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.53,1:14:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,To get beyond the experiencer, just to the witness observer,\Njust to witness and observe without necessarily extracting experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.93,1:14:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Experiencing.\NSo the experiencer is the leading edge of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.00,1:14:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So meditative and contemplative, then, is to be with consciousness-awareness without\Nnecessarily experiencing the content of consciousness-awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.59,1:14:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds tricky, but one time it suddenly comes to you that one is the witness of it,\None is the observer.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.87,1:14:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't know.\NBut you don't necessarily have to experience it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.29,1:14:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to juice it.\NSo the ego, to survive, is addicted to experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.68,1:15:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And it survives because of the juice it gets out of that.\NSo we eventually transcend that through faith, hope, devotion, and prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.24,1:15:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, please take me, help me go beyond that.\NThrough humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.38,1:15:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Through self-realization and awareness.\NThrough mindfulness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.63,1:15:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We get to the observer-witness.\NThat is not difficult to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.06,1:15:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That can be done.\NAnd because we notice that below the thinking mind, there is a silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.53,1:15:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you focus on the silence, you'll notice that your mind isn't saying anything about\Nwhat's going on out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.80,1:15:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego jumps in, tries to fill it up with something.\NBut if you lose your attraction to the titillation and novelty of the mind's thinkingness, trying
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.41,1:16:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to extract experiencing, you'd be satisfied with having no experience, thoughts, feelings,\Nor anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.01,1:16:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of you say, well, what do you feel about that?\NI don't have any feeling about it at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.16,1:16:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Feeling about what?\NThe world's coming to an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.16,1:16:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's coming to an end.\NOh, oh, yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.16,1:16:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what do you know about that?\NIt's not to allow.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.16,1:16:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not to allow.\NIt's not to allow.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.37,1:16:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not to allow.\NIt's not to allow.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.09,1:16:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not to allow.\NSKYPETS
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.71,1:16:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's coming to an end.\NAlcohol is coming to an end, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.65,1:16:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's coming to an end.\NGod's coming to an end anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.89,1:16:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a year before 12 anyway.\NDecember 21, 2012.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.03,1:16:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay your bills before then.\NThe world's always coming to the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.90,1:16:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always a guy on the sidewalk with a sandwich board.\NRepent.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.15,1:16:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is coming to an end.\NAnd the fact that he comes from the Mayan calendar doesn't give it any more truth than
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.19,1:17:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it does.\Nfirm people. I mean, the world is coming to an end in the year 2012. Oh boy. I got a whole
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.67,1:17:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,refrigerator full of pickled herring and I want to eat it. Cramming them down. And then you get\Nto December 22nd, 2012, and you're not dead. You think, Christ, I ate up all the pickled herring.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.62,1:17:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Spent all my money. Oh, so if the world doesn't come to an end, that's what you got to worry\Nabout. If the world comes to an end, you'll have no problems. If the world's not coming to an end,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.52,1:17:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,worry about that. Actually, it doesn't make any difference. So all right. So humility then\Nand mindfulness, you become aware of what your mind is doing. It's always anticipating the future,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.80,1:18:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to get one up on the future, and clinging to it.\NAnd to the past. So therefore, the present moment is ignored because your mind is either clinging to
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.58,1:18:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,what just happened, trying to juice it, or it's anticipating what might happen, whether we're all\Ngoing to expire in 2021, for instance. So these eventually lead you through mindfulness then,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.41,1:18:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,through divine stupidity, and through choice, then reflection and meditation,\Nthat I'm describing become common. The mind generally focuses on the small self, the ego, on gain,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.85,1:18:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,desire, accepting and rejecting. I like and I don't like. I like and I don't like. I like it and I don't like it.\NSomebody say, what do you think of that movie? Frankly, I don't think about it at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.37,1:19:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, I don't think about it. All right. So these character traits carry you this.\NPerseverance.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.61,1:19:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Perseverance and commitment and acceptance. And the power of declaration, which we haven't spoken about yet.\NThere is intention. And then there is something beyond even intention that activates intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.78,1:19:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is to make a declaration and then live by the declaration.\NHow many people have made a declaration about the purpose of their life?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.10,1:19:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow. Quite a few. All right. Pretty sophisticated group.\NIt is.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.10,1:19:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,To declare that one is the servant of God and that one's purpose is to realize the divinity of one's own inner self\Nand the divinity of Almighty God and to become one with God.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.26,1:20:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a declaration made by, hmm, I hate to ask the number,\Ndeclaration made by less than a half of one percent of humanity, less than a quarter of a percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.93,1:20:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A fraction. It's really a fraction of one percent.\NEver reached the evolution of consciousness where they make a declaration that the meaning and purpose of my life
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.93,1:20:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is to serve God, to become one with God, to become enlightened.\NAnd as we said, I think in power versus force, the number of people interested in reaching enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.09,1:20:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is less than one in ten million. You know, what do you want to do here in this world?\NSo these are the spiritual options.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.50,1:20:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So life in this world is purgatorial in my view of it.\NPurgatorial. You don't have to worry about purgatory later. You're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.38,1:21:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing purgatory? You suffer out bad karma.\NAnd you have the option to choose options for good karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.38,1:21:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that all purgatory is? So why be afraid of purgatory?\NBecause you're in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.54,1:21:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, if breaking your ankle doesn't hurt, then you'd be in a different place.\NIn this realm, purgatory, if you break your ankle, it hurts.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.60,1:21:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So, in a celestial realm, you don't have any ankle to break.\NThe fact that negativity means this, in this world, people bemoan it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.06,1:21:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to repeat, this is not a celestial realm. This is not a celestial realm.\NAs a realm, my inner experience of it, however, can be heavenly.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.06,1:21:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, by perseverance, by acceptance, by declaration.\NSo, declaration is very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.22,1:22:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you declare who you are and the purpose of your life,\Nyou've made a very major impact on what your consciousness is going to be attracted to.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.76,1:22:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be attracted to those things that bring about enlightenment.\NAnd it's going to be not attracted.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.82,1:22:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean, does not mean to have an aversion.\NAn aversion is something different.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.20,1:22:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It means you're not attracted to it.\NNo, I'm differentiating.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.06,1:22:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,To not be attracted is different than aversion.\NBecause aversion, like attraction, is a trap.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.29,1:22:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,To have neither attraction nor diversion.\NBut just have no interest in a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.35,1:22:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's lots of movies that come up and are popular and lots of things on television and all.\NThat I just don't have an interest in.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.48,1:22:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I just say, I'm not really interested in that.\NWhen I was 22, I would have been.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.48,1:23:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God for old age, I tell you.\NIt solves a lot of problems, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.34,1:23:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't remember who you were mad at.\NI knew I was mad at somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.30,1:23:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't remember what I was mad at about.\NI was mad at about something.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.30,1:23:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of consciousness, then,\Nis how you're going to experience the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.04,1:23:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you see you do with your personal experience\Nis what you see happening in society
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.04,1:23:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is to dramatize the story into a narrative.\NUsually a poor me or a bad you narrative.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.03,1:23:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a way of describing things now coming out of relativity.\NThere's no descriptions of relativity.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.45,1:23:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only narratives.\NThere are only narratives.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.45,1:24:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the story that your mind makes up about it.\NAnd, of course, the dramatization of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.45,1:24:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,To make a bigger impact on others.\NAll of this comes out of meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.54,1:24:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What does a thing mean?\NAnd we'll get more into that next time.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.57,1:24:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning cannot be understood without context.\NThat's why the cynic, you know, can't get anywhere with reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.60,1:24:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because...\NWhat he doesn't see is that it's the meaning,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.14,1:24:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the significance, the implication,\Nthe non-linear, non-languaged understanding and comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.62,1:24:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So all spiritual understanding is revealed in its abstract meaning,\Nout of which you have an interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.52,1:24:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Use various adjectives, inferences, connotations, attitudes, etc.\NBut those are all elaborations.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.74,1:25:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't just what happens, the significance, the content, the context.\NBut what is the meaning of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.74,1:25:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could take all of life and you say,\NWhat is interesting about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.74,1:25:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing's really interesting about it except what it means.\NIf it's lacking meaning, then it's just a passing animal experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.97,1:25:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal sees a rubber ball go by.\NHe sees a cat go by.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.97,1:25:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But he doesn't get any meaning out of that.\NMeaning, what is the meaning?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.06,1:25:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So our significance then arises from our meaning.\NWhat is the meaning of our existence?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.06,1:25:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of our existence?\NWhat is the value of existence itself?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.06,1:25:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it so great to even be a human being?\NIt would be better to be a kitty and just purr all day.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.58,1:25:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,See a dog and wag its tail and be happy.\NWhat's the meaning?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.91,1:25:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind's proclivity for error.\NWe got one more slide after this?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.30,1:26:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NGo faster.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.30,1:26:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind's proclivity for error.\NWe mentioned that 50% of blog sites are fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.74,1:26:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't write me an angry hot letter tonight.\NOver 50% of the information in blogger land is fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.47,1:26:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 50% of all that bloggerism is fallacious to begin with.\NNot to mention its intent, which is often vicious, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.81,1:26:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This is about what you would expect.\NNow, in law courts, you'll find out there's a 50% error in lineup identifications.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.35,1:26:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, these are the possible suspects.\NIs this the man you saw on the street?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.35,1:27:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,50% error.\NI saw the crime committed by a guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.89,1:27:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he this one, this one, this one, this one?\NHe's this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.40,1:27:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,50% likelihood that they will be wrong.\NHow many guys in the...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.88,1:27:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatchamacallit project have been released from prison?\NWhat's that called?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.20,1:27:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mercy Project or something?\NI forget how many.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.09,1:27:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,90 of them, at least, on death row.\NAnd then when the DNA came out, they found that they were on death row, that they were actually innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.09,1:27:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And most of them were convicted due to a false identification.\NSo, if you can't even believe your eyes, well, can you believe?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.82,1:27:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Even your eyes lie to you.\NEven your eyes lie to you 50-50.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.82,1:27:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And bloggerdom is 50-50.\NWhat's going to happen to mankind?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.82,1:28:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Buried by bloggerism.\NDeath by bloggerism.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.23,1:28:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No, go to number four.\NI mean the next, last one.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.06,1:28:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NDeath by bloggerism.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.06,1:28:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the decline of consciousness of mankind.\NWe went from 207 back down to 204.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.11,1:28:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the decline of consciousness level of the Western world, which is currently in free fall.\NAnd the decline of consciousness level in America itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.34,1:28:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, America went from 426 to 421.\NMankind went back down.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.43,1:28:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He went from 190 to 205.\NThen he went to 207.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.43,1:28:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he's back down to 204.\NAnd the Western world is also declining.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.43,1:28:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NThe reason we can't see what's real is because of bias.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.87,1:29:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the negativity of the intention.\NBecause of how you're aligned.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.16,1:29:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That determines your preferences.\NAnd that determines your attractions and your aversions.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.16,1:29:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I always think if people don't like the things I say, please don't read the book.\NWho asked you to read the book?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.35,1:29:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It says Dio on the first page and he's offended because you're defending God.\NCan't you read the first page, you idiot?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.01,1:29:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the intention to disparage truth, divinity, etc. blinds people.\NAnd they end up writing the dumb blogs at 1 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.95,1:29:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Naivete. What is real?\NNaivete is another downside.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.95,1:29:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's overcome by familiarity, interpretation, sophistication.\NSo many objections.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.95,1:30:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Many objections to truth are really facetious.\NAnd every once in a while we'll get one.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.34,1:30:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just plain facetious.\NFacetious.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.34,1:30:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NFacetious.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.59,1:30:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And understanding is also reflective of intelligence.\NIntelligence is an overall state.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.45,1:30:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just one's IQ.\NIntelligence operationally depends on your education.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.45,1:30:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How you've been indoctrinated.\NHow you've been programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.45,1:30:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you've had the good fortune to have been brought up in a family that respects morality, ethics, etc.\NThen you're going to be more aware of when it's out.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.67,1:30:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Social influence, cultural norms, and expectations depend on many factors.\NYou see people think, oh, how wonderful my mind is.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.67,1:30:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what you're thinking has to do with how you were brought up.\NHas to do with your neuronal connections.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.67,1:31:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Has to do with the social class, your sex, your gender.\NPolitical indoctrination, the way you're brought up.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.95,1:31:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Has to do with the way things are labeled.\NDepends on whether they're popular.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.02,1:31:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And not all depends on the media hype and the glamour.\NWhat is truth in today's world is what people believe because it has been pounded into your head via the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.37,1:31:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Repetitious memes reappear, reappear, reappear.\NAnd therefore, what people believe is true is how they've been indoctrinated.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.37,1:31:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultural norms and expectations.\NLabeling, popularity, and how much media hype it gets.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.88,1:31:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in today's world, for media hype, people will sell anything.\NWill they not?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.46,1:31:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Nude pictures of themselves or the most god awful information about their life.\NBecause it gets you on the daily news.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.46,1:32:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I feel sorry for that.\NI feel sorry for the people who become victims.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.52,1:32:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you can see they're victims not only of their own egotism, but of all their controllers.\NAll the people who are getting multi-millions, feeding dispersion to the dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.55,1:32:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So they really get fed to the dogs for a price.\NAnd those are the social influences.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.38,1:32:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention.\NYou see how things change.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.38,1:32:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're active.\NIf you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.38,1:32:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you inspect things.\NIf you enjoy them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.38,1:32:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember them.\NFind fault with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.38,1:32:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Criticize them.\NOr want to destroy them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.54,1:32:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So these all are values coming out of intention.\NSo if you're trying to extract the truth about something, your intention about it is already interpreting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.67,1:32:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So some of the funny blogs we get, or one of those things you get on the internet machine,\Nhas to do with the person's intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.67,1:33:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,To become facetious in order to ridicule something.\NAnd you can see the departure from truth and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.77,1:33:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of this, there are in our world, diminishers and expanders.\NI'm just showing you all the processes, the chances of knowing what is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.57,1:33:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got four pages of things that can destroy that capacity.\NPeople can generally be divided into minimizers and diministers.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.36,1:33:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Minimizers and expanders.\NMinimizers say, oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.45,1:33:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And expanders say, wow.\NWow, look at that Denmark vendor.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.79,1:33:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And a diminisher will say, oh, that's nothing.\N$50 worth of paint will fix it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.14,1:33:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NSo you can diminish or expand.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.50,1:33:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's not within one's conscious control.\NThe mind just automatically tends to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.75,1:34:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to have a mind that depends on your childhood experiences.\NWhether spilling milk was a big deal, or it was a minor deal, don't worry about it, I'll mop it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.75,1:34:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Or whether it was a big deal.\NSo diminishing and expanding then comes from childhood training
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.75,1:34:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of what your parents consider to be emotionally important.\NAnd they do this by dramatizing it, exaggerating it, or minimizing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.03,1:34:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Also how you interpret things depends on your overall mental capacity.\Nthe old Freudian balance of the ego. The Freudian view of the ego is somewhat
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.13,1:34:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,different. It has a more positive view of the ego. It sees that as the mental\Ncapacity to balance the id, that's one's emotional animal instincts, and the
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.81,1:35:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,superego, which is one's conscience. So in classical Freudian analysis, your ego's\Ncapacity to get away from excessive guilt, excessive guilt, at the same time
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.48,1:35:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,not give in to your id, which is just an instinctual animal. You can't run around\Nraping people. On the other hand, you can't kill yourself because you made a
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.02,1:35:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,slight mistake. So the Freudian ego is defined as reality testing, the capacity\Nfor reality testing. Balancing the id, which is a crazy animal and is out to
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.33,1:35:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,kill you and everybody else, or the superego, which is punitive. And I think\Nas I've said, I'm not going to go into too much detail about that, but I think
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.07,1:35:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,as I've said, I'm not going to go into too much detail about that, but I think\NI've told you, when I was young, I had to go for counseling, for, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.31,1:35:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,scrupulosity. The slightest infraction of truth in my viewpoint was like\Nunforgivable blot on your soul, and God could see this black spot. So you lived
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.86,1:36:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in dread of having even a passing sinful thought. All right, so generally then, the\Ncapacity for reality testing, the superego, which is an instinctual animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.35,1:36:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,capacity for understanding reality is a balance of mental, emotional health, where\Nyou have balance, you have maturity, and unconscious psychological factors, such
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.91,1:36:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,as poor self-esteem and things like this. Yep. Whether the absolute reality is\Nallness or nothingness is a differentiation which we've made in more
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.42,1:36:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced lectures. And then we come to the last one, which I don't understand at\Nall, and therefore I'll explain it to you. And that is, what is the absolute reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.52,1:36:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is, what is the absolute reality? And that is, what is the absolute reality?\NAnd that is, what is the absolute reality? And that is, what is the absolute reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.88,1:36:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is, what is the absolute reality? And that is, what is the absolute reality?\NThe so-called quantum Zeno effect. Yeah, x-what is the absolute reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.44,1:36:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the more often an\NAn absolute reality Ori Magajan
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.37,1:36:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,equation is chosen, the more likely the\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.53,1:36:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so-called quantum Zeno\NThe so-called quantum Zeno
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.19,1:36:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,x- vertex\Nthe
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.57,1:36:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,enser으룪\Noption
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.51,1:36:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,no effect. The more often an option is chosen, the more likely the option will\Nbe chosen again.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.45,1:37:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this has to do with intention and commitment then.\NThe more often you choose to forgive, the more likely you will be to forgive.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.62,1:37:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get this extract\NEven though statistically the options are mathematically the same, length of time
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.58,1:37:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the same, the likelihood is that consciousness, because of its own nature, because you choose\Na certain option, you are more likely to choose that option again.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.52,1:37:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So the more often you choose a benign option, a benign way, you say, well, I could be seeing\Nthis such and such.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.46,1:37:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you get into a negative thought or a negative fix, you ask yourself, well, how\Ncould I be seeing this?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.12,1:37:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, that's part of the Course in Miracles, and one reason it works.\NYou ask the Holy Spirit to recontextualize it so you see it differently, so you see it
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.94,1:37:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,through the eyes of forgiveness, and you see that whatever you're upset about is because\Nyou've stopped time at some particular point, and when you expand it beyond that particular
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.41,1:38:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,point and you see it's sort of an evolutionary revelation, you see the innocence of what\Nyou were just upset about.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.39,1:38:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're really asking God to do is to recontextualize.\NThe way you're experiencing and comprehending a situation, and that takes you out of right
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.24,1:38:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and wrong and condemnation of yourself and others, and that takes you out of guilt and\Nanger and hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.30,1:38:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the recontextualization then is done as an option because that's your commitment to\Nbe that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.87,1:38:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now another person doesn't, you know, another person who is not spiritually oriented just\Nsees something and hates it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.28,1:38:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels justified, and that's okay with them.\NBut as you grow spiritually, the negatives are no longer so pleasantly tolerated.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.10,1:38:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you find they're not welcome anymore.\NIt's like you're used to beautiful music, and some awful music comes on, and you're
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.62,1:39:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,used to beauty now.\NThe worst music in the world is on the Weather Channel.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.70,1:39:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to do something to help God and humanity, write the Weather Channel.\NThey have the worst God-awful.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.40,1:39:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Disharmonic, harmonious music I've ever heard.\NI'll say this to them, turn it down, I can't stand the music.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.30,1:39:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They have the unhearing ear for bad, bad music.\NAnyway, we'll forgive them because after all, the only reason we're looking at it is to
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.74,1:39:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,find out if it's going to rain on the day of the lecture anyway.\NAnd our intention must be okay because so far we've had good weather.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.31,1:39:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've given altogether about 50 all-day lectures locally since 2002.\NWe've given another 40 of them or so elsewhere in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.99,1:40:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll be approaching, we'll have given maybe before long 100 all-day lectures, including\Ndescriptions, slides, lectures, explanations, and sharing oneself to the best of one's ability.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.27,1:40:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is one's, that comes out of one's declaration of one's intention.\NWhich is the same intention I had as a physician because I practiced medicine for 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.54,1:40:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was to be helpful in every way that you could to the people entrusted to your care\Nbecause you know you're answerable to God for what you did with this person.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.62,1:40:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that you're answerable to God.\NAnd so to be answerable to God for one's life then almost guarantees spiritual purification.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.18,1:40:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?\NReally?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.84,1:40:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?\NReally?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.88,1:40:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that you're dedicated to God and that you're answerable to God, then you become\Nvery aligned with truth and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.18,1:41:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The people that are dangerous in this world are ones who do not believe they're answerable\Nto God.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.80,1:41:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They're dangerous, yeah.\NAnd you can trust people who realize, accept, I'm answerable to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.10,1:41:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is a constant state during these lectures, and I realize I'm answerable to God for any\Nerror I make.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.42,1:41:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared to death of making an error.\NSo you take responsibility for the truth of what you teach others, and people who won't
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.20,1:41:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,take responsibility for the truth of their own teaching are very dangerous.\NBut to be responsible.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.60,1:41:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So I accept responsibility for the truth of all I have conveyed, and I accept responsibility\Nif I have made any errors, because I've done them unwittingly.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.02,1:42:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So I feel the teacher should recommit his devotion to the truth and to his students\Nand restate what his commitment is, what the commitment of his life is.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.89,1:42:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So as each one of us does that by declaration, then.\NWe become responsible.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.86,1:42:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We become that, which counterbalances the negativity of the world.\NBecause how many people are willing to do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.38,1:42:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Only a group like this is willing to really stake your answerability to God for the integrity\Nby which you do your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.24,1:42:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean you can't make a mistake, but it was an honest mistake.\NAnd even if it was not an honest mistake, you then admit that it was not an honest mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.53,1:42:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I contrive that.\NIn order to feel sorry for myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.37,1:42:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I make everybody else look bad, you see.\NSo even then, the truth gets you out of a falsehood, out of an error, by telling the
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.03,1:42:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,truth about it.\NYou say, well, my ego just wanted to be right about it, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.41,1:43:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And I mean, the Weather Channel does that bad music.\NI don't know, I remember the director of music there, I don't know, would never have passed
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.95,1:43:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the seashore music ability test with, I don't know, I never would have made it.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.34,1:43:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NLet's see our last slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.34,1:43:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to shut them up otherwise.\NAh!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.34,1:43:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,God, this comes from my wonderful editor.\NShe found this somewhere out there in blogger land or internet land, WW internet world.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.76,1:44:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think it's so wonderful.\NSo I may not have gotten it across verbally, one of the questions in the last lecture,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.04,1:44:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,she said, I said, oh my God, I have missed completely.\NMaking the difference between appearance and essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.43,1:44:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What percentage of politicians, let's ask something about politicians.\NThe majority of the politicians lie routinely.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.02,1:44:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's part of their job.\NTherefore, please don't quote a politician as the source of authority.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.96,1:44:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The politician is supposed to make things work by whatever means, you understand?\NHis commitment is not a spiritual one.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.66,1:44:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no point in making a politician wrong.\NHe has to make the thing work by whatever means he can to make it work, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.73,1:44:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And if he tells everybody, if they do it this way, this is going to happen, everybody's\Ngoing to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.91,1:45:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And as far as he sees, he's fulfilling the good and the good is the fulfillment of a\Ncertain specified objective.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.35,1:45:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So a spiritual person has a different whole set of what is integrous, what is truth, what\Nis honesty and what is reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.11,1:45:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But isn't that adorable?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.79,1:45:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I just get such a kick out of that, see?\NAnd the reason I emphasize this so much is because I was surprised when we calibrated
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.66,1:45:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Wolf and Sheep's clothing.\NI was surprised.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.95,1:45:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It only came out at 120.\NI said, wow, that's worse than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.00,1:45:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because a lot of political bullshit is, calibrates at 190.\NI thought, well, it's going to be 190 coming out of prideful egotism, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.72,1:45:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it came out at 120.\NWhich 120 then means.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.73,1:45:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That it is the hiding place of evil itself, that what you're looking at is evil.\NThat's why 120.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.04,1:46:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why it's so important to become sophisticated and realize essence is one thing,\Nperception is another.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.13,1:46:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This calibrates at 120.\NI just think that's very, very significant.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.78,1:46:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a serious error, see?\NIt's not just a minor one to be, to misperceive.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:12.24,1:46:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To take advantage of it.\NIt's a serious error.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.24,1:46:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just a minor one.\NI think that the Komodo dragon is safe because you're a humanitarian, you love all of nature,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.71,1:46:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,blah, blah, blah.\NDoesn't mean you can step in the cage with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.10,1:46:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So the downside of Western civilization is it's lost that capacity.\NWe have to be nice to all the Komodo dragons and invite them here.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.87,1:46:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're just nice animals.\NJust nice animals.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:41.59,1:46:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So that error is quite severe at 120.\NTherefore, I thought this.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.99,1:46:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This teaches in one glance, you know, what it would take a number of lectures to get\Nacross to many people.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.78,1:47:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself have been deceived by the sheep's clothing.\NAnybody else here ever been deceived by the sheep's clothing?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.61,1:47:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo I think, I thought one picture is worth a thousand words.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.07,1:47:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why we brought it to people's awareness.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.99,1:47:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, now let's see.\NWhere are we on time?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.56,1:47:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I get you to watch.
